<title type="html"><![CDATA[OTP EPROM Question]]></title>

<content type="html" xml:base="http://forums.nesdev.com/viewtopic.php?t=8290&amp;p=86033#p86033"><![CDATA[
If you have a dumper of some sort dump the roms and compare the dump to what it should be.  Any patterns or misplaced byte sequences you find are the keys to figuring out where the error is.<br /><br />Does your programmer verify after writing the ROM?  Can you read the ROM after programming it and compare the output to what you gave as the import ROM image?  Then you could at least find out if your error is in the wiring or programming.<p>Statistics: Posted by <a href="http://forums.nesdev.com/memberlist.php?mode=viewprofile&amp;u=4832">infiniteneslives</a> — Tue Nov 08, 2011 9:43 pm</p><hr />
]]></content>
